<br>
I've been hunting in Kedge with my wife. Every time I logged on, I would go kill the placeholder for the priest of najena in Unrest. Then I'd go underwater and kill swordfish for 55 minutes. I kept the time on a stopwatch. Then I'd come back up and kill the placeholder again.<br>
<br>
Also, every morning I'd get up, kill the placeholder, camp. Take a shower and get ready for work, then kill the placeholder again.<br>
<br>
I did this routine for a week, and killed maybe 15 placeholders. I recommend this method of camping him to anyone. There was rarely somebody else there camping him. And once you kill the placeholder, only YOU know when he's going to respawn. Others will come look and find nothing there. This way, you don't have to endure <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> hours</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of boring, pointless camping.<br>
<br>
Last night, I was sitting there medding, counting the seconds until he respawned, when I saw the message &quot;priest of najena begins to cast a spell.&quot; I used an earth pet on him. It was a close battle, with me trying to unload cinder bolts into him faster than he could heal. Fortunately, right as I ran out of mana, he finally keeled over and gave up his key. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 35th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureaperrp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ReaperRP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/00 6:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Got my mystic cloak</span><hr size=1> Congratulations.<br>
